 <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg></li>\n <li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/propertyIsEnumerable\"><code>Object.prototype.propertyIsEnumerable()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/create\"><code>Object.create()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/getOwnPropertyNames\"><code>Object.getOwnPropertyNames()</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Beschreibung","id":"beschreibung"},{"text":"Beispiele","id":"beispiele"},{"text":"Polyfill","id":"polyfill"},{"text":"Spezifikationen","id":"spezifikationen"},{"text":"Browser Kompatibilität","id":"browser_kompatibilität"}],"summary":"Die Methode Object.values() gibt ein Array mit den Eigenschaftswerten eines gegebenen Objekts in der selben Reihenfolge wie eine for...in-Schleife sie geben würde zurück (Der Unterschied ist dabei, dass eine for-in Schleife zusätzlich die Eigenschaften der Protoype-Kette aufzählt).","popularity":0.0013,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Object.values()","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Object.values()","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"Object.values()","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Object.values()","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Object.values()","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"Object.values()","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"Object.values()","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"Object.values()","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"de/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/object/values","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/de/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/object/values/index.html","last_commit_